{
  prompt: """How do I linearly interpolate between two values."""

  solution: """
    0 = x
    
    0.01 ;; interpolation factor
    Math.Lerp(x  100)
    > x

    x
    Log("value")
  """

  explicit: """
    0 = x
    
    0.01 ;; interpolation factor
    Math.Lerp(First:x  Second:100)
    > x

    x
    Log(Prefix:"value")
  """

  explanation: """
    Math.Lerp is a Maths Shard which takes the interpolation factor as input and will lineraly interpolate between the the value in the First parameter to
    the value in the Second Paramter.
  """

  tag: "  #Maths"
}